<div class="section faq wf-section">
  <div class="container w-container">
    <div class="row faq-wrapper">
      <div id="w-node-c64315b9-ab89-1550-7546-1accf2bdcca3-6f389a2f" class="column faq-heading-wrapper">
        <h2 class="section-heading">FAQ</h2>
        <p class="subheading">Frequently asked questions</p>
      </div>
      <div id="w-node-c64315b9-ab89-1550-7546-1accf2bdcca8-6f389a2f" class="column faq-content-wrapper">
        <div class="faq-wrapper">
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="330b93b6-4694-0fe8-cfce-5538aa28f23a" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. Who can mint Fuji assets?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. Anyone can open a new contract to borrow a synthetic asset offered on the platform, after locking L-BTC as collateral in a covenant contract, the asset can be minted.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="ac9bc06e-9ff9-34a6-d427-0232fb84f344" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. How to send, receive and store Fuji assets?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. Any wallet that has integrated the Liquid Network can store, send and receive Fuji assets to any address, in a peer to peer fashion.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="2a6a8362-be02-5df7-649b-dbee1a5396aa" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. Who are the parties involved in the contract?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. The user locking the collateral is called <span class="text-bold-italic">sponsor</span> and Fuji is always the <span class="text-bold-italic">issuer</span> and the <span class="text-bold-italic">liquidator</span>. The liquidation process is performed as soon as the value of collateral is below the <span class="text-bold">minimum collateralization requirement</span> and that is attested by an oracle with the use of a cryptographic signature.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="66ff12ab-c4e2-60b5-2937-9ccbcf33fd57" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. How can the sponsor get back the collateral locked in the covenant?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. The sponsor can always redeem the entire collateral, upon burning the same amount of Fuji asset as was issued for this collateral, plus a small payout for redemption of 0.25% payable in L-BTC.<br><br>In case of the price of the collateral falling below the contract <span class="text-bold">minimum collateralization requirement</span>, the liquidator will claim the collateral upon burning the Fuji asset and presenting the oracleâ€™s signed message.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="3ed927f2-1754-eb86-1cdf-9c14a12c0ef7" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. As a sponsor, why would I ever lock Bitcoin to mint a Fuji asset?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer margin-bottom-12">There are many reasons, but they can be:</p>
              <ol class="text-white no-margin">
                <li>You need a lot of Fuji assets (for running a market on TDEX or to use in lending schemes etc..) and it is not practical to buy on the market because of the fees or low liquidity.</li>
                <li>If you believe that your Bitcoin price will rise you can use it to mint a Fuji asset, then use that asset to buy more Bitcoin - so basically you can use minting as leverage.</li>
                <li>If the Fuji asset trading price is above the reference index you can mint Fuji to sell it on exchanges.</li>
              </ol>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="f0d07e89-fb98-2cf6-11dd-0f49dfd8d0d2" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. What is the minimum collateralization requirement?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. Each sponsor must, at all times, maintain collateral such that the ratio of deposited collateral to asset settlement value is greater than the collateralization requirement of 150%, otherwise the collateral will be liquidated. To prevent liquidation, the sponsor can top-up the collateral via a single transaction that combines redeem and the issuance in one event, and does not require payout to the issuer.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="5c3b84eb-8b95-8db0-6ade-fa4769dd937e" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. Can someone else beside the original sponsor redeem the collateral upon burning a Fuji asset?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. No. In future contract upgrades it will be possible for the sponsor to irrevocably grant redemption rights to other entities, using a special control token.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="56cb26f7-903b-f15e-b5b3-843ba1d7ea67" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. How to verify that Fuji is not issuing Fuji assets without being backed by collateral?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. The mint and burn process of Fuji assets are always NON confidential (ie. visible on the Liquid Network) and therefore <a href="/">easy to verify</a> the supply and the collateral. This minimizes the risk of Fuji losing credibility and reputation.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="cc742c5b-28ba-bf59-5609-41b3b6552bc3" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. If the Fuji asset represents a stock or security, can I vote or receive dividends?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. No, a Fuji asset does not grant any rights on the underlying reference asset, only tracks the price.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="72a20815-bdae-587b-6553-1fe20931da6b" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. How is the price guaranteed to be 1 to 1 with the reference asset?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. It is expected that sponsor and liquidator incentives of redemption and liquidation, will make the asset price to closely follow the one of the underlying reference asset, plus anyone can mint new Fuji at the current reference price, using arbitrage opportunities to balance the price on decentralized exchanges.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="6ce07ff5-5e5b-0cc4-99c1-7678c7d7d247" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. If the value of the collateral exceeds the collateralization requirement, is the sponsor forced to redeem?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. No, there is no obligation to redeem the collateral and close the contract.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
          <div data-hover="false" data-delay="0" data-w-id="660e1f87-37aa-d2ba-fe27-e5654b2aa7fb" style="height:92px" class="faq-item w-dropdown">
            <div class="faq-question-wrapper w-dropdown-toggle">
              <div style="-webkit-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-moz-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);-ms-transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0);transform:translate3d(0, 0, 0) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0, 0)" class="accordion-icon w-icon-dropdown-toggle"></div>
              <h5 class="faq-question-heading">Q. The liquidation is tied to a single Oracle service decided in advance?</h5>
            </div>
            <nav class="faq-answer-wrapper w-dropdown-list">
              <p class="faq-answer">A. All available Oracle services can be used to trigger the liquidation process. Each oracle service must sign his own price and include a timestamp in the message.</p>
            </nav>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
